<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: Cricket board in Pounds 58.5m
television deal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The BBC and BSkyB are to pay a combined Pounds 58.5m for a four-year deal
with the Test and County Cricket Board to show home Test matches and
domestic games. This compares with the board's Pounds 15m television income
from the last three years.
</TEXT>
