FT  16 AUG 94 / International Company News: Singapore bank ahead 14% as loan
base grows
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Development Bank of Singapore (DBS), the island republic's largest bank, has
announced pre-tax profits for the six months to end-June of SDollars 311m
(USDollars 206m), a 14 per cent rise on the corresponding period last year.
DBS said group net interest income was SDollars 332m, a rise of 22 per cent.
It said the increase was due to improved net interest margins and an
expansion of its loan base.
The bank reported a 47 per cent increase in income on fees and commissions
to SDollars 124m, mainly due to higher income from merchant banking and
investment banking.
Per share earnings rose from 61 Singapore cents to 71 cents. over the
period.
The dividend is unchanged at 8 cents.
