<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: PNG gold mine back in operation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KENNETH GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Porgera gold mine in Papua New Guinea, one of the largest in the world
outside of South Africa and an important source of revenue for the PNG
government, resumed full production at the weekend.
Operations were halted on August 2 by an explosion at an explosives facility
near the mine which killed 11 people.
On Saturday Sir John Kaputin, PNG's Minister of Mining and Petroleum, gave
approval for full production after recommissioning processes last week
confirmed that the mine and plant were operating safely.
Placer Pacific, the project manager, says it will take several months to
repair the damage to the mine. Porgera produces nearly 1.5m troy ounces of
gold annually and, apart from collecting royalties, the government has a 25
per cent stake.
</TEXT>
