<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 94 / UK Company News: BOC buys Dutch group for Pounds 10.8m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLARE GASCOIGNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BOC, the industrial gases and healthcare company, has bought a Dutch
equipment supplier for Fl 29.4m (Pounds 10.8m).
The Calumatic group, which supplies filling, sterilising and capping lines
to the pharmaceutical industry, will be integrated with Edwards Freeze
Drying, part of BOC's vacuum technology division and a supplier of freeze
driers to the pharmaceutical industry. The acquisition will be funded by
cash, a proportion of which is deferred and contingent on future
performance.
Mr Danny Rosenkranz, managing director, said the acquisition 'allows us to
develop our freeze-drying business'. The new business, BOC Edwards
Calumatic, will be able to provide complete packaging solutions for a
variety of injectable formulations.
BOC is implementing a three-year restructuring, and made an Pounds 85m
provision in its latest accounts, Pounds 60m of which was for the healthcare
business. It reported a fall in pre-tax profits to Pounds 169.3m, compared
with Pounds 261.6m, in the nine months to June 30.
BOC shares rose 7p to 732p.
</TEXT>
