<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Andrews Sykes net assets cut by Pounds 4m
after valuation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Andrews Sykes Group, the specialist industrial services company, announced
yesterday that since the 1993-94 results were announced, on August 1, the
result of an actuarial valuation of its UK pension schemes had been received
resulting in a drop in the current surplus from Pounds 5.9m to Pounds 2.4m.
The company said that the valuation reinforces the board's belief that it
was inappropriate to bring this surplus onto the balance sheet, where it had
been held since 1990, as it did not represent a readily available tangible
asset.
As a result, final results for the year will include a prior year adjustment
to reflect a change of accounting policy, excluding the brought forward
surplus from the balance sheet.
The loss before tax of Pounds 4.7m and the gearing ratio of 256 per cent
(excluding the surplus) are unchanged, but net assets at March 31 are
reduced by Pounds 4m to Pounds 6.7m.
</TEXT>
