FT  16 AUG 94 / Prisons on market testing shortlist
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Prison Service has drawn up a shortlist of 12 prisons and nine open
prisons which have the greatest potential for improved performance as
candidates for market testing later this year, John Authers writes.
The list is based on statistics for escapes, assaults, prisoner activity,
time unlocked and cost per place. Each of the prisons has a month to provide
more qualitative information which might explain their performance.
The board will then choose one or two prisons to be tested against the
market by the end of September.
The 12 are: Aylesbury, Coldingley, Erlestoke, Everthorpe, Feltham, Hollesley
Bay, Huntercombe, Northallerton, Reading, Rochester, Shepton Mallet and
Styal. The nine open prisons to be subjected to more detailed qualitative
analysis are: Ford, Hewell Grange, Kirkham, Leyhill, Morton Hall, North Sea
Camp, Spring Hill, Standford Hill and Sudbury/Foston.
