<HEADLINE>
FT  16 AUG 94 / Carlos 'the Jackal' flown to Paris after Sudan arrest
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Carlos 'the Jackal', the notorious terrorist and guerrilla, is being held in
Paris after being captured in Sudan.
Carlos, pictured above in Sudan before his arrest, is linked to many of the
world's bloodiest terrorist attacks over the past two decades, including the
1972 massacre of 11 Israeli athletes at the Munich Olympics, the 1974
takeover of the French embassy in the Hague, and the 1976 hijacking to
Entebbe, Uganda, of an Air France airliner.
He has eluded the authorities by moving from country to country, notably
Syria, Libya and Hungary, where he was given refuge by the former communist
regime in the late 1970s.
However, since the mid-1980s, with the collapse of communism and the
improvement of relations in the Middle East, Carlos has found refuge more
difficult, French officials said. Report, Page 16
