FT  15 AUG 94 / French employment up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Further evidence emerged yesterday of the recovery in the French economy
with the news that the number of salaried employees, rose by 60,000, or 0.4
per cent, to just over 9m in the second quarter of this year, according to
the Employment Ministry. This continues the upward trend of the first
quarter, when salaried employment rose by 0.2 per cent. It follows the news
that the overall level of unemployment experienced its biggest fall for four
years in June with the number of jobless dropping by 13,000 to 3.33m, or
12.6 per cent of the workforce. Economic growth in France during the first
quarter was higher than expected at 0.7 per cent rather than its original
estimate of 0.5 per cent.
