<HEADLINE>
FT  15 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: Win for Schumacher
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Germany's Michael Schumacher cemented his position as Formula One
championship leader when he won the Hungarian grand prix in a Benetton.
Britain's Damon Hill, driving a Williams Renault, was second and
Schumacher's teammate, Jos Verstappen of the Netherlands, third. Black flag
at Monza, Page 2
</TEXT>
