<DATE>940815
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  15 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The EMS had a fairly turbulent week, prompted by higher interest rates from
two countries outside the grid, Sweden and Italy. The result was a large
increase in the position of the strongest currency against the weakest,
generalised D-Mark strength, and the Irish punt being displaced at the top
of the grid by the Dutch guilder. The D-Mark also climbed above the Belgian
franc. Currencies, Page 29
</TEXT>
